INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (92,1,'2009-03-20 09:28:28','2009-03-19 21:28:28','','Get in touch',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-3','','','2009-03-20 09:28:28','2009-03-19 21:28:28','',45,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/45-revision-3',0,'revision','',0),(3,1,'2009-03-20 08:26:18','2009-03-19 20:26:18','','Home',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','home','','','2009-03-20 08:26:41','2009-03-19 20:26:41','',0,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=3',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2009-03-20 08:26:11','2009-03-19 20:26:11','','Home',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','3-revision','','','2009-03-20 08:26:11','2009-03-19 20:26:11','',3,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?p=4',0,'revision','',0),(5,1,'2009-03-20 08:26:18','2009-03-19 20:26:18','','Home',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','3-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 08:26:18','2009-03-19 20:26:18','',3,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?p=5',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2009-03-20 08:29:44','2009-03-19 20:29:44','<h2>Professional improvisors for nearly 30 years</h2>\r\nTheatre Sports was first introduced to Christchurch in 1987, and a number of enthisiasts were quick to take the plunge performing in teams on a Sunday night. These people included Kirsty Gillespie, Patrick Duffy and the Ross Gumbley, now Artistic Director at the Court Theatre. Each scene was judged for entertainment, storyline and technique, with the two most highly-scoring teams performing for the entire evening while other teams were eliminated.\r\n\r\nAfter about six months, some of the more accomplished improvisers were invited to take part in a late night improv show called <a href=\"/shows/scriptless\">Scared Scriptless</a>, starting at 11pm. The improvisers were less constrained by the Theatre Sports format, and, over the years, developed a number of other show formats within this time slot and within the broader Court Theatre programme. A number of well-known actors and comedians honed their improv skills at the Court, including Greg Cooper, Cal Wilson, KC Kelly, and the late Kevin Smith. In 1994, the Court Jesters took on 16 of the world\'s best Theatre Sports teams, and were crowned World Champions.\r\n\r\nIn 2006, a new and larger audience was introduced to Scared Scriptless when the show was brought forward to 10pm. It now sells out almost every week and is proud to be Australasia\'s longest-running comedy show.\r\n\r\nThe Court Jesters also perform over 100 shows a year off-site, bringing their peculiar brand of comedy and skills to corporate events, parties and conferences.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/about/us\">Meet the Jesters…</a>','Who we are',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','about','','','2009-04-19 16:11:06','2009-04-19 04:11:06','',0,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=6',200,'page','',0),(7,1,'2009-03-20 08:29:19','2009-03-19 20:29:19','','Who we are',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','6-revision','','','2009-03-20 08:29:19','2009-03-19 20:29:19','',6,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2009-03-20 08:32:01','2009-03-19 20:32:01','Click on the Jesters below to find out a bit more about us.\r\n\r\n[headshots]','Meet the Jesters',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','us','','','2009-03-22 21:45:44','2009-03-22 09:45:44','',6,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=8',210,'page','',0),(9,1,'2009-03-20 08:31:48','2009-03-19 20:31:48','','Meet the Jesters',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','8-revision','','','2009-03-20 08:31:48','2009-03-19 20:31:48','',8,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/8-revision',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2009-03-20 08:33:54','2009-03-19 20:33:54','Many product launches, television commercials and advertising roles want more than just a pretty face. We are happy to put forward talented actors and improvisors for your casting requirements. Please contact Kirsty at <a href=\"mailto:jesters@courttheatre.org.nz \">jesters@courttheatre.org.nz </a>with the brief for your next film, photoshoot, TVC, product launch, or voiceover, and she will be happy to submit people with the right look and the right skills.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/casting.jpg\" alt=\"Some of the Court Jesters\" title=\"Some of the Court Jesters\" width=\"632\" height=\"200\" class=\"size-full wp-image-187\" />\r\n','Casting information',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','casting','','','2009-04-25 13:20:05','2009-04-25 01:20:05','',6,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=10',220,'page','',0),(11,1,'2009-03-20 08:33:41','2009-03-19 20:33:41','','Casting Information',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','10-revision','','','2009-03-20 08:33:41','2009-03-19 20:33:41','',10,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/10-revision',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2009-03-20 08:34:22','2009-03-19 20:34:22','<h2>Entertaining Christchurch since 1971</h2>\r\n<p>The Court Theatre is Christchurch\'s only, and New Zealand\'s foremost, professional theatre company, offering entertainment of the highest quality throughout the year.</p>\r\n<p>Founded by Yvette Bromley QSM and Mervyn Thompson in 1971, The Court fast became a central part to the cultural life of Christchurch, the Canterbury region, and New Zealand as a whole, and has gone on to become the most successful arts organisation in New Zealand.</p>\r\n<p>Housed in the heart of Christchurch City\'s Arts Centre since 1976, The Court operates two auditoria. Court One seats 291 in an intimate, \"semi-thrust\" stage and is in operation throughout the year, staging at least eight productions, with each season totalling approximately 270 performances annually. Each season provides a mix of New Zealand works, modern international theatre, and classics.</p>\r\n<p>The Forge seats 123 in a \"box\" setting, and is the staging ground for challenging international, local and devised works presented to an adventurous audience wanting edgy and contemporary theatre.</p>\r\n<p>The Court Theatre employs professionals from around the country and internationally, and is dedicated to fostering and supporting local artists. It sustains a full-time professional staff and an ensemble acting company and is administered by The Court Theatre Trust (incorporated under the Charitable Trusts Act 1959). At any one time there can be up to 100 people working full-time at The Court Theatre.</p>\r\n<p>For more information, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.courttheatre.org.nz\" target=\"_blank\">Court Theatre\'s own website</a>.</p>\r\n','The Court Theatre',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','theatre','','','2009-04-25 13:11:53','2009-04-25 01:11:53','',6,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=12',230,'page','',0),(13,1,'2009-03-20 08:34:12','2009-03-19 20:34:12','','The Court Theatre',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','12-revision','','','2009-03-20 08:34:12','2009-03-19 20:34:12','',12,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/12-revision',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2009-03-20 08:34:22','2009-03-19 20:34:22','','The Court Theatre',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 08:34:22','2009-03-19 20:34:22','',12,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/12-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2009-03-20 08:33:54','2009-03-19 20:33:54','','Casting Information',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 08:33:54','2009-03-19 20:33:54','',10,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/10-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(16,1,'2009-03-20 08:29:44','2009-03-19 20:29:44','','Who we are',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','6-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 08:29:44','2009-03-19 20:29:44','',6,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/6-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2009-03-20 09:17:43','2009-03-19 21:17:43','<h2>Sometimes, even we have scripts.</h2>\r\n<p>OK, so we\'re most famous for <a href=\"/shows/scriptless\">Scared Scriptless</a>, <del>New Zealand</del> Australasia\'s longest-running comedy show.</p>\r\n<p>But did you know the Jesters have performed in a huge variety of plays, musicals and films, both scripted and unscripted, and are about the most versatile company of actors you\'re likely to meet?</p>\r\n<p>In addition to <a href=\"/shows/past\">previous shows we\'ve put on as a company</a>, members of the Court Jesters have held roles in shows up and down the country, as well as overseas, for audiences of all ages and theatrical tastes.</p>\r\n<p>Check out <a href=\"/shows/upcoming\">what we\'ve got coming up</a>: there\'s sure to be something for everyone.</p>','Our Shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','shows','','','2009-05-07 20:05:49','2009-05-07 08:05:49','',0,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=17',300,'page','',0),(18,1,'2009-03-20 09:17:08','2009-03-19 21:17:08','','What we do',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','17-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:17:08','2009-03-19 21:17:08','',17,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/17-revision',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2009-03-20 09:17:43','2009-03-19 21:17:43','','What we do',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','17-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 09:17:43','2009-03-19 21:17:43','',17,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/17-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2009-03-20 09:19:26','2009-03-19 21:19:26','<h2>New Zealand\'s longest-running comedy show</h2>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"highlight\">Due to popular demand, from 23 May we\'ll be offering a <strong>second show every Saturday night!</strong> Now you have even more chance to see New Zealand\'s most popular comedy show.</p>\r\n\r\nA favourite of Christchurch audiences for nearly twenty years, Scared Scriptless combines fast-paced, off-the-cuff theatre with just the right amount of audience interaction and the Court Jesters\' own brand of razor-sharp wit. Based on audience suggestions, the players offer a completely new show each Friday night for less than the price of a movie!\r\n\r\nDepending on when you visit, you could see:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Theatre Sports match:</strong> Two or more teams battle it out head-to-head for some ephemerally important but ultimately meaningless trinket — or simply for the love of you, the audience!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Improvised songs and musicals:</strong> With the aid of our extremely talented musical improvisors, the Jesters make beautiful music before your eyes.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Scriptless Idol:</strong> A large group of players form temporary alliances to escape elimination and vie for the title of Scriptless Idol. Only you have the power to decide who is worthy of such an honour!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quick-fire games and scenes:</strong> From old favourites like Word At A Time Story and Alphabet to experimental, Frankensteinian games of our own devising like Sean Connery Is My Milkman and How Many Dudes?, you\'re guaranteed to see something at Scriptless you\'ve never witnessed before.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith over 300 shows under our belt as a company, we\'ve still never played the same scene twice!\r\n\r\n<strong>Scared Scriptless is on every Friday night (except public holidays) at the Court Theatre. To book, call the Box Office on 963 0870, or </strong><a href=\"https://www.patronbase.com/_CT/Productions/6093/Performances\"><strong>book online</strong></a><strong>.</strong>','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','scriptless','','','2009-04-25 12:52:08','2009-04-25 00:52:08','',17,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=20',310,'page','',0),(21,1,'2009-03-20 09:19:22','2009-03-19 21:19:22','','Improvisation',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:19:22','2009-03-19 21:19:22','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/20-revision',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2009-03-20 09:20:19','2009-03-19 21:20:19','<h2 id=\"eels\">The Early Early Late Show</h2>\r\nThe Forge at The Court Theatre proudly presents a return season of <cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> – a showcase of the Court Jesters’ unique brand of fast-paced, furiously funny improvised comedy in a family-friendly format and time.\r\n\r\n“The Jesters have been enjoying record attendances at <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite>,” says Artistic Director (and founding Court Jester) Ross Gumbley, “<cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> is a great way to display their skills to a brand-new audience – one that might not be able to come to on a Friday at 10pm or worried about the content a ‘late-night’ show may have. This is family-friendly entertainment that introduces the uniquely interactive experience that is improvised theatre.”\r\n\r\nThe current season of <cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> is currently scheduled to run from April 30 until May 16, with performances at 8pm on Thursdays, Fridays and Saturdays. All tickets are the “low, low price” of $15.\r\n\r\n<cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> evolved in 2006 when a touring show withdrew unexpectedly. Gumbley recalls during a discussion of the problem, “Someone asked ‘How do we create a show out of nothing at the last minute?’ That’s when we realised that that’s what the Jesters do every week.” <cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> was conceived, cast, staged and promptly sold out.\r\n\r\nOn the heels of this success, the Jesters have become key drawcards in The Forge, creating shows like <cite>Radio Ha Ha</cite>, <cite>Chatterbox</cite>, <cite>Pulp William</cite> (which will tour the country and take part in the NZ International Comedy Festival 2009), <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite> and <cite>A Very Merry Scriptless</cite> to critical and audience acclaim. While quick to praise these shows, Gumbley likes the return to “no frills” improvised theatre. “Improvisation is at its best when it is at its simplest – using an audience suggestion (or volunteer) to conjure something out of thin air. It’s theatrical magic.”\r\n\r\n<strong><cite>The Early Early Late Show</cite> opens on April 30 and runs for a strictly limited season.</strong>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-243\" title=\"Pulp William\" src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/pw-walking.jpg\" alt=\"Pulp William\" width=\"256\" height=\"267\" /></div>\r\n\r\n<h2 id=\"pulp-william\">Pulp William</h2>\r\n\r\nTake Christchurch comedy troupe The Court Jesters, mix them up with William Shakespeare, Quentin Tarantino and the insanity of New Zealand’s longest-running comedy show, <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite>, and you’ve got an improvised show of epic proportions: <cite>Pulp William</cite>.\r\n\r\nConceived and performed by Brendon Bennetts, Dan Bain and Javier Jarquin, this “Shakespearean crime-thriller comedy” has been aided and abetted by veteran improviser, writer and director (and previous member of The Court Jesters) Greg Cooper.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, <cite>Pulp William</cite> enjoyed a successful season at The Forge at The Court Theatre, hailed by critics and audiences alike. In 2009 the cast will travel the country, performing a short return season in Canterbury before playing Auckland as one of only two Christchurch entries in the NZ International Comedy Festival (the other being Dan Bain and Javier Jarquin’s stand-up comedy show <cite>Orphans of Comedy</cite>).\r\n\r\nCooper immediately saw the comic appeal of <cite>Pulp William</cite>. “It takes the style and language of Shakespeare and pumps it up with the characters and the pop-culture references of Tarantino,” says Cooper, “then ups the ante by being entirely improvised”.\r\n\r\nFor those unfamiliar with the unique insanity that is improv, Cooper is happy to explain, saying, “The cast weave seemingly random suggestions together, spouting Shakespearean verse all the way. Like <cite>Pulp Fiction</cite>, the narrative might not be linear - it may, for instance, flash back in time to show how one character developed an audience-suggested fear of clowns. The result is a plot with more twists than a night at Jack Rabbit Slims”.\r\n\r\nRehearsals have been packed with star-crossed lovers, bad-ass gangsters, Mexican stand-offs, Italian surnames, cunning plots, poison, handguns, sonnets and protracted speeches with extended metaphors. The cast call the result a “leaner, meaner, faster and funnier production than anything we’ve done before”. Those worried about bad language need not worry – all swearing is Shakespearean, so “only those fluent in 16th Century English will be offended”, adds Cooper.\r\n\r\nShakespeare scholars, film buffs or fans of improv comedy, PULP WILLIAM has something for everyone.\r\n\r\n<q>“Manic madness that never missed a beat... forsooth ’twas devilish fun.”</q> – <cite>PRESTO Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“Packs enough comedy to appeal to anyone”</q> – <cite>Canta Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“A goodly chuckle indeed”</q> – <cite><a href=\"http://www.theatreview.org.nz/reviews/review.php?id=1275\">Theatreview</a></cite>\r\n<h3>Canterbury Tour</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>May 13:  Ngaio Marsh Theatre, University of Canterbury; 7:00pm - book at Unimart</li>\r\n	<li>May 14:  Rangiora Town Hall, Rangiora; 7:30pm - book at The Court Theatre</li>\r\n	<li>May 15:  The Gaiety, Akaroa; 7:30pm - book at The Information Centre</li>\r\n	<li>May 16:  The Loons, Lyttelton; 8pm - book at <a href=\"http://www.theloons.co.nz\">www.theloons.co.nz</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTickets: All Canterbury Tickets $15\r\n<h3>Nz Comedy Festival</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>May 20-23:  The Transmission Room; 10pm - Book at TICKETEK (service fee will apply)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTickets: Adults $25 / Concessions $20/ Groups $18\r\n\r\nFor more information, images or interviews, or to arrange reviewers tickets, contact:\r\n\r\nJeff Clark, Communications Manager\r\nPh: 963 0899\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:education@courttheatre.org.nz\">communications@courttheatre.org.nz</a>','Upcoming shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','upcoming','','','2009-05-10 13:01:59','2009-05-10 01:01:59','',17,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=22',320,'page','',0),(23,1,'2009-03-20 09:19:37','2009-03-19 21:19:37','','Corporate entertainment',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','22-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:19:37','2009-03-19 21:19:37','',22,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/22-revision',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2009-03-20 09:20:43','2009-03-19 21:20:43','<h2>Scared Scriptless</h2>\r\n<em>10pm every Friday night</em>\r\n<p>New Zealand’s longest-running comedy show (established in 1990), <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite> is fast-paced, furiously funny improvisation at its best as an MC and cast of improvisers tackle whatever the audience throws at them. It’s entertainment with no scripts and no safety nets.</p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/shows/scriptless\">More about Scared Scriptless</a>\r\n<h2>The Early Early Late Show</h2>\r\n<em>22 June - 29 July 2007 and 30 April – 9 May 2009</em>\r\n\r\n<p>Very, very funny at an early, early time with plenty of audience participation and laughs for all ages in a show that you can take the whole family to see and still have them home in time for bed. If you\'re scared of Scared Scriptless, The Early Early Late Show is the perfect introduction to the Jesters’ brand of improvised mayhem.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A Very Merry Scriptless</h2>\r\n<em>Annual</em>\r\n\r\nMasters of improvised mayhem The Court Jesters gave their fast-paced, furiously funny brand of comedy a festive feel in A Very Merry Scriptless, with content suitable for the whole family. This holiday-themed improvised show is a theatrical Christmas cracker for all ages.\r\n\r\nIn 2006 the show followed a fun format of short scenes in the traditional <cite>Scriptless</cite> style. In 2007 it was a “Celebrity Christmas Special” hosted by Scott Koorey. In 2008 the Jesters took on Scrooge with an improvised reinterpretation of Dickens’ <cite>Christmas Carol</cite>. In 2009 they take on the Nativity itself.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/pulp-william.jpg\" alt=\"Pulp William\" title=\"Pulp William\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-165\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Pulp William</h2>\r\n<em>29 February – 29 March 2008 and on tour in 2009</em>\r\n\r\nThree performers break out of their cages after being locked up with Shakespeare’s Complete Works and a set of Tarantino DVDs to create a unique mix of star-crossed lovers, bad-ass gangsters, Mexican stand-offs, Italian surnames, cunning plots, poison, handguns, sonnets and fast-paced dialogue laden with pop culture references and extended metaphors - all in a plot with more twists than a night at Jack Rabbit Slims. It’s an improvised comedy mash-up that blows audiences away.\r\n\r\n<q>“Forsooth \'twas devilish fun.”</q> – <cite>PRESTO Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“Packs enough comedy to appeal to anyone”</q> - <cite>CANTA</cite>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/uncut.jpg\" alt=\"Scriptless Uncut\" title=\"Scriptless Uncut\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-161\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Scriptless Uncut</h2>\r\n<em>16 May – 14 June 2008</em>\r\n\r\nWith the glitz and glamour of a Hollywood awards ceremony, The Jesters romp across genres, styles and the bounds of political correctness to create anything from art-house, melodrama and independent film to schlock horror, science fiction and big-budget blockbusters, armed with only their wits (and audience suggestions) to guide them. <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite> is a love letter to an industry that shoots too many pictures and not enough actors.\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/chatterbox.jpg\" alt=\"Chatterbox\" title=\"Chatterbox\" width=\"280\" height=\"145\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-168\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Chatterbox</h2>\r\n<em>31 August — 29 September 2007</em>\r\n\r\nThe stars of today are lampooned by the stars of tomorrow as The Court Jesters get up close and personal with local celebrities. After a live interview with Artistic Director Ross Gumbley, four of our top improvisers replay stories from the lives and careers of these famous Cantabrians. Guests include Garry Moore, Margaret Mahy, Steve Gurney, David McPhail and Ruth Dyson.\r\n<h2>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</h2>\r\n<em>7 – 19 July 2007</em>\r\n\r\nEver wondered what your Mad Old Auntie keeps in her trunk?  For the three kids in <cite>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</cite>, it’s everything they need to escape the boredom of a rainy day and get carried away on a magical adventure that has them cruising the world in a boat or a plane, defending castles, or riding in wagon trains with cowboys and indians! No two shows are the same as the audience help decide what happens next in a unique adventure in storytelling using the magic of imagination.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/haha.jpg\" alt=\"Radio Ha Ha\" title=\"Radio Ha Ha\" width=\"150\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-166\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Radio Ha Ha</h2>\r\n<em>27 April — 26 May 2007</em>\r\n\r\nA rapid-fire, off-the-cuff 1930s radio show shaped entirely around audience suggestions to create news, interviews and thrilling serials that never seen – or heard - before. Packed with thrills and spills and complete with live sound effects and music, this loving homage to the golden age of the wireless proved so popular that it was aired on Radio NZ National.','Past Shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','closed','open','','past','','','2009-04-25 13:32:09','2009-04-25 01:32:09','',17,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=24',330,'page','',0),(25,1,'2009-03-20 09:20:32','2009-03-19 21:20:32','','Fundraisers',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:20:32','2009-03-19 21:20:32','',24,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/24-revision',0,'revision','',0),(26,1,'2009-03-20 09:20:19','2009-03-19 21:20:19','','Corporate entertainment',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 09:20:19','2009-03-19 21:20:19','',22,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/22-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2009-03-20 09:20:43','2009-03-19 21:20:43','','Fundraisers',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-2','','','2009-03-20 09:20:43','2009-03-19 21:20:43','',24,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/24-revision-2',0,'revision','',0),(28,1,'2009-03-20 09:22:04','2009-03-19 21:22:04','<strong>Did you know</strong> that the professional entertainers who present New Zealand\'s longest running comedy show, <a href=\"/shows/scriptless\">Scared Scriptless</a>, can also entertain at your party or event?\r\n\r\nHow about an improvised show during your dinner, personalised to your business using your suggestions and volunteers?\r\n\r\nOr for a theme night or product launch with a difference we provide:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MCs to keep your event on track</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/events/themes\">Roaming characters</a> in costume, greeting your guests or customers</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/events/fundraisers\">Fundraising options</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"/events/packages\">View our list of packages</a> for inspiration, or <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> to find out how we can make your event a night to remember -- for all the right reasons!','Your next event',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','events','','','2009-05-07 20:12:51','2009-05-07 08:12:51','',0,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=28',100,'page','',0),(29,1,'2009-03-20 09:21:42','2009-03-19 21:21:42','','Your next event',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','28-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:21:42','2009-03-19 21:21:42','',28,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/28-revision',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:11','2009-03-19 21:23:11','Improvised theatre is at the core of the Court Jesters\' performances. Our\r\nprofessional MCs and quick-witted performers help you to laugh at yourselves\r\nwith stories and scenes tailored specifically to your group.\r\n<h2>Improvised Comedy Shows</h2>\r\nBased on the infamous Scared Scriptless format, our improvised comedy shows\r\nuse audience suggestions and volunteers to spontaneously create fast-paced,\r\nfuriously funny comedy for everyone. A guaranteed crowd pleaser and our most\r\npopular form of entertainment.\r\n\r\nWhile every show is unique, we also have some show concepts that are also\r\nvery popular:\r\n<h3>AshVegas</h3>\r\nLet has-been host Dirk Shiny bring you some song and dance routines worthy of the Ash Vegas stage for dinner and dancing with a difference!\r\n<h3>Murder at the Winery</h3>\r\nA who-dunnit where the audience decide who-dunnit without having to dress up and be characters themselves. Enjoy fine wine, food, and solve the crime of the century.\r\n<h3>World\'s Worst Waiters</h3>\r\nThey look like the real thing, but good service is the last thing on their minds. Watch your friends react to the world\'s worst waiters, who will be more entertaining than the main course.\r\n<h3>Back to School</h3>\r\nYour own children will seem like angels when the kids and teachers from \'Constant High\' learn one of life\'s most amusing lessons.\r\n<h3>What the Dickens?</h3>\r\nYour favourite Dickens characters create a Scrooge-like Christmas.\r\n<h3>Bad Santa</h3>\r\nWhat goes on when the Christmas tree lights go out?\r\n\r\nPerfect for conferences, weddings, schools, clubs, anniversaries, corporates, executive retreats, hens\' nights &amp; Bar Mitzvahs (yes, we <em>have</em>)!\r\n\r\nFor more information on any of our packages or offerings, or to book your next event, please <a href=\"/contact\">get in touch</a> today!','Packages',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','packages','','','2009-05-07 20:10:27','2009-05-07 08:10:27','',28,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=30',110,'page','',0),(31,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:00','2009-03-19 21:23:00','','Packages',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','30-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:23:00','2009-03-19 21:23:00','',30,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/30-revision',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:29','2009-03-19 21:23:29','Outrageous characters meet and greet your guests to provide an unforgettable\r\ninteractive experience and a perfect ice-breaker for any occasion.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medieval Madness</li>\r\n	<li>High tea complete with a poacher, gamekeeper &amp; Lady Muck</li>\r\n	<li>Lord of the Rings</li>\r\n	<li>Hillbillies</li>\r\n	<li>Rock stars or Rocky Horror</li>\r\n	<li>Fairy tale, fantasy or futuristic</li>\r\n	<li>Bad Santa, Elves, and a Christmas tart</li>\r\n	<li>Cops and robbers</li>\r\n	<li>Detectives and gangsters</li>\r\n	<li>Ancient Roman</li>\r\n	<li>Superheroes</li>\r\n	<li>Cowboys and Indians</li>\r\n	<li>Men In Black or bouncers</li>\r\n	<li>Mad scientists</li>\r\n	<li>Pirates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nFor more information on any of our themes or offerings, or to book your next event, please <a href=\"/contact\">get in touch</a> today!\r\n\r\n\r\n','Themes & Characters',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','themes','','','2009-05-07 20:30:24','2009-05-07 08:30:24','',28,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=32',120,'page','',0),(33,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:24','2009-03-19 21:23:24','','Characters',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','32-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:23:24','2009-03-19 21:23:24','',32,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/32-revision',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:49','2009-03-19 21:23:49','<strong>Fundraising?</strong> Your own private Scared Scriptless Show is one of the easiest fundraisers to organise and sell.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You choose the night (usually a Sunday or Thursday).</li>\r\n	<li>We provide the actors, theatre, tickets, tech, and bar facilities.</li>\r\n	<li>We charge you $10 + GST a ticket.</li>\r\n	<li>You sell the tickets at your own price and the difference is your profit. <strong>Easy!</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Court 1</strong> has 290 seats and you will be charged for 250 @ $10 + GST\r\n\r\n<strong>The Forge</strong> has 123 seats and you will be charged for 120 @ $10 + GST\r\n\r\nFor tickets sold at $15 your organisation will make $450 – $1000; for tickets sold at $20 you will make $1000 – $2400 (depending on the number of tickets sold).\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/contact\">Get in touch today</a> for more information or to book your fundraiser with the Court Jesters.','Fundraisers',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','fundraisers','','','2009-04-23 18:49:36','2009-04-23 06:49:36','',28,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/?page_id=34',130,'page','',0),(35,1,'2009-03-20 09:23:47','2009-03-19 21:23:47','','MCs',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','34-revision','','','2009-03-20 09:23:47','2009-03-19 21:23:47','',34,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/34-revision',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2009-03-20 09:24:29','2009-03-19 21:24:29','Improving spontenaity has many benefits for any business that values fresh ideas and a customer service focus. The Court Jesters have worked with franchisees, corporates, and MBA students to allow individuals to be more confident when outside their comfort zone. We also specifically offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Team building</li>\r\n	<li>Presentation skills</li>\r\n	<li>Improvisation training</li>\r\n	<li>Body language</li>\r\n	<li>Public speaking</li>\r\n	<li>Role play scenarios for employment interviews</li>\r\n	<li>Theatre Sports tutoring</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur interactive training techniques put words into action! <a href=\"/contact\">Call us<