 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/uncut.jpg\" alt=\"Scriptless Uncut\" title=\"Scriptless Uncut\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-161\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Scriptless Uncut</h2>\r\n<em>16 May – 14 June 2008</em>\r\n\r\nWith the glitz and glamour of a Hollywood awards ceremony, The Jesters romp across genres, styles and the bounds of political correctness to create anything from art-house, melodrama and independent film to schlock horror, science fiction and big-budget blockbusters, armed with only their wits (and audience suggestions) to guide them. <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite> is a love letter to an industry that shoots too many pictures and not enough actors.\r\n<h2>Chatterbox</h2>\r\n<em>31 August — 29 September 2007</em>\r\n\r\nThe stars of today are lampooned by the stars of tomorrow as The Court Jesters got up close and personal with local celebrities. After a live interview with Artistic Director Ross Gumbley, four of our top improvisers replay stories from the lives and careers of these famous Cantabrians. Guests include Garry Moore, Margaret Mahy, Steve Gurney, David McPhail and Ruth Dyson.\r\n<h2>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</h2>\r\n<em>7 – 19 July 2007</em>\r\n\r\nEver wondered what your Mad Old Auntie keeps in her trunk?  For the three kids in <cite>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</cite>, it’s everything they need to escape the boredom of a rainy day and get carried away on a magical adventure that has them cruising the world in a boat or a plane, defending castles, or riding in wagon trains with cowboys and indians! No two shows are the same as the audience help decide what happens next in a unique adventure in storytelling using the magic of imagination.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/haha.jpg\" alt=\"Radio Ha Ha\" title=\"Radio Ha Ha\" width=\"150\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-166\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Radio Ha Ha</h2>\r\n<em>27 April — 26 May 2007</em>\r\n\r\nA rapid-fire, off-the-cuff 1930s radio show shaped entirely around audience suggestions to create news, interviews and thrilling serials that never seen – or heard - before. Packed with thrills and spills and complete with live sound effects and music, this loving homage to the golden age of the wireless proved so popular that it was aired on Radio NZ National.','Past Shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-14','','','2009-04-19 16:44:03','2009-04-19 04:44:03','',24,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/24-revision-14',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2009-04-25 13:30:53','2009-04-25 01:30:53','<h2>New Zealand\'s longest-running comedy show</h2>\n\n<p class=\"highlight\">Due to popular demand, from 23 May we\'ll be offering a <strong>second show every Saturday night!</strong> Now you have even more chance to see New Zealand\'s most popular comedy show.</p>\n\nA favourite of Christchurch audiences for nearly twenty years, Scared Scriptless combines fast-paced, off-the-cuff theatre with just the right amount of audience interaction and the Court Jesters\' own brand of razor-sharp wit. Based on audience suggestions, the players offer a completely new show each Friday night for less than the price of a movie!\n\nDepending on when you visit, you could see:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Theatre Sports match:</strong> Two or more teams battle it out head-to-head for some ephemerally important but ultimately meaningless trinket — or simply for the love of you, the audience!</li>\n	<li><strong>Improvised songs and musicals:</strong> With the aid of our extremely talented musical improvisors, the Jesters make beautiful music before your eyes.</li>\n	<li><strong>Scriptless Idol:</strong> A large group of players form temporary alliances to escape elimination and vie for the title of Scriptless Idol. Only you have the power to decide who is worthy of such an honour!</li>\n	<li><strong>Quick-fire games and scenes:</strong> From old favourites like Word At A Time Story and Alphabet to experimental, Frankensteinian games of our own devising like Sean Connery Is My Milkman and How Many Dudes?, you\'re guaranteed to see something at Scriptless you\'ve never witnessed before.</li>\n</ul>\nWith over 300 shows under our belt as a company, we\'ve still never played the same scene twice!\n\n<strong>Scared Scriptless is on every Friday night (except public holidays) at the Court Theatre. To book, call the Box Office on 963 0870, or </strong><a href=\"https://www.patronbase.com/_CT/Productions/6093/Performances\"><strong>book online</strong></a><strong>.</strong>','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-autosave','','','2009-04-25 13:30:53','2009-04-25 01:30:53','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/20-autosave',0,'revision','',0),(171,1,'2009-03-20 11:36:58','2009-03-19 23:36:58','','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-6','','','2009-03-20 11:36:58','2009-03-19 23:36:58','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/20-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(172,1,'2009-04-19 17:09:05','2009-04-19 05:09:05','<h2>New Zealand\'s longest-running comedy show</h2>\r\nA favourite of Christchurch audiences for nearly twenty years, Scared Scriptless combines fast-paced, off-the-cuff theatre with just the right amount of audience interaction and the Court Jesters\' own brand of razor-sharp wit. Based on audience suggestions, the players offer a completely new show each Friday night for less than the price of a movie!\r\n\r\nDepending on when you visit, you could see:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Theatre Sports match:</strong> Two or more teams battle it out head-to-head for some ephemerally important but ultimately meaningless trinket — or simply for the love of you, the audience!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Improvised songs and musicals:</strong> With the aid of our extremely talented musical improvisors, 