ll be offering a <strong>second show every Saturday night!</strong> Now you have even more chance to see New Zealand\'s most popular comedy show.</p>\r\n\r\nA favourite of Christchurch audiences for nearly twenty years, Scared Scriptless combines fast-paced, off-the-cuff theatre with just the right amount of audience interaction and the Court Jesters\' own brand of razor-sharp wit. Based on audience suggestions, the players offer a completely new show each Friday night for less than the price of a movie!\r\n\r\nDepending on when you visit, you could see:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Theatre Sports match:</strong> Two or more teams battle it out head-to-head for some ephemerally important but ultimately meaningless trinket — or simply for the love of you, the audience!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Improvised songs and musicals:</strong> With the aid of our extremely talented musical improvisors, the Jesters make beautiful music before your eyes.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Scriptless Idol:</strong> A large group of players form temporary alliances to escape elimination and vie for the title of Scriptless Idol. Only you have the power to decide who is worthy of such an honour!</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Quick-fire games and scenes:</strong> From old favourites like Word At A Time Story and Alphabet to new and experimental, Frankensteinian games of our own devising like Sean Connery Is My Milkman and How Many Dudes?, you\'re guaranteed to see something at Scriptless you\'ve never witnessed before.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWith over 300 shows under our belt as a company, we\'ve still never played the same scene twice!\r\n\r\n<strong>Scared Scriptless is on every Friday night (except public holidays) at the Court Theatre. To book, call the Box Office on 963 0870, or </strong><a href=\"https://www.patronbase.com/_CT/Productions/6093/Performances\"><strong>book online</strong></a><strong>.</strong>','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-9','','','2009-04-25 12:50:31','2009-04-25 00:50:31','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/20-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(185,1,'2009-04-25 13:11:22','2009-04-25 01:11:22','','The Court Theatre',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'The Court Theatre','inherit','open','open','','court','','','2009-04-25 13:11:22','2009-04-25 01:11:22','',12,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/court.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(186,1,'2009-04-05 13:16:50','2009-04-05 01:16:50','<h2>Entertaining Christchurch since 1971</h2>\r\nThe Court Theatre is Christchurch\'s only, and New Zealand\'s foremost, professional theatre company, offering entertainment of the highest quality throughout the year.\r\n\r\nFounded by Yvette Bromley QSM and Mervyn Thompson in 1971, The Court fast became a central part to the cultural life of Christchurch, the Canterbury region, and New Zealand as a whole, and has gone on to become the most successful arts organisation in New Zealand.\r\n\r\nHoused in the heart of Christchurch City\'s Arts Centre since 1976, The Court operates two auditoria. Court One seats 291 in an intimate, \"semi-thrust\" stage and is in operation throughout the year, staging at least eight productions, with each season totalling approximately 270 performances annually. Each season provides a mix of New Zealand works, modern international theatre, and classics.\r\n\r\nThe Forge seats 123 in a \"box\" setting, and is the staging ground for challenging international, local and devised works presented to an adventurous audience wanting edgy and contemporary theatre.\r\n\r\nThe Court Theatre employs professionals from around the country and internationally, and is dedicated to fostering and supporting local artists. It sustains a full-time professional staff and an ensemble acting company and is administered by The Court Theatre Trust (incorporated under the Charitable Trusts Act 1959). At any one time there can be up to 100 people working full-time at The Court Theatre.\r\n\r\nFor more information, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.courttheatre.org.nz\" target=\"_blank\">Court Theatre\'s own website</a>.','The Court Theatre',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','12-revision-6','','','2009-04-05 13:16:50','2009-04-05 01:16:50','',12,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/12-revision-6',0,'revision','',0),(187,1,'2009-04-25 13:19:38','2009-04-25 01:19:38','','Some of the Court Jesters',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'Some of the Court Jesters','inherit','open','open','','casting','','','2009-04-25 13:19:38','2009-04-25 01:19:38','',10,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/casting.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(188,1,'2009-04-23 18:55:20','2009-04-23 06:55:20','Many product launches, television commercials and advertising roles want more than just a pretty face. We are happy to put forward talented actors and improvisors for your casting requirements. Please contact Kirsty at <a href=\"mailto:jesters@courttheatre.org.nz \">jesters@courttheatre.org.nz </a>with the brief for your next film, photoshoot, TVC, product launch, or voiceover, and she will be happy to submit people with the right look and the right skills.','Casting information',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','10-revision-5','','','2009-04-23 18:55:20','2009-04-23 06:55:20','',10,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/10-revision-5',0,'revision','',0),(189,1,'2009-04-25 13:23:09','2009-04-25 01:23:09','','Our biggest fan',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','fan','','','2009-04-25 13:23:09','2009-04-25 01:23:09','',79,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/fan.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(190,1,'2009-04-25 13:28:58','2009-04-25 01:28:58','','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','scriptless-1','','','2009-04-25 13:28:58','2009-04-25 01:28:58','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/scriptless-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(191,1,'2009-04-25 13:28:59','2009-04-25 01:28:59','','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','scriptless-2','','','2009-04-25 13:28:59','2009-04-25 01:28:59','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/scriptless-2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(192,1,'2009-04-25 13:29:00','2009-04-25 01:29:00','','Scared Scriptless',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','scriptless-3','','','2009-04-25 13:29:00','2009-04-25 01:29:00','',20,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/scriptless-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(193,1,'2009-04-19 16:45:55','2009-04-19 04:45:55','<h2>Scared Scriptless</h2>\r\n<em>10pm every Friday night</em>\r\n<p>New Zealand’s longest-running comedy show (established in 1990), <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite> is fast-paced, furiously funny improvisation at its best as an MC and cast of improvisers tackle whatever the audience throws at them. It’s entertainment with no scripts and no safety nets.</p>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/shows/scriptless\">More about Scared Scriptless</a>\r\n<h2>The Early Early Late Show</h2>\r\n<p>22 June - 29 July 2007 and 30 April – 9 May 2009</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Very, very funny at an early, early time with plenty of audience participation and laughs for all ages in a show that you can take the whole family to see and still have them home in time for bed. If you\'re scared of Scared Scriptless, The Early Early Late Show is the perfect introduction to the Jesters’ brand of improvised mayhem.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A Very Merry Scriptless</h2>\r\n<em>Annual</em>\r\n\r\nMasters of improvised mayhem The Court Jesters gave their fast-paced, furiously funny brand of comedy a festive feel in A Very Merry Scriptless, with content suitable for the whole family. This holiday-themed improvised show is a theatrical Christmas cracker for all ages.\r\n\r\nIn 2006 the show followed a fun format of short scenes in the traditional <cite>Scriptless</cite> style. In 2007 it was a “Celebrity Christmas Special” hosted by Scott Koorey. In 2008 the Jesters took on Scrooge with an improvised reinterpretation of Dickens’ <cite>Christmas Carol</cite>. In 2009 they take on the Nativity itself.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/pulp-william.jpg\" alt=\"Pulp William\" title=\"Pulp William\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-165\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Pulp William</h2>\r\n<em>29 February – 29 March 2008 and on tour in 2009</em>\r\n\r\nThree performers break out of their cages after being locked up with Shakespeare’s Complete Works and a set of Tarantino DVDs to create a unique mix of star-crossed lovers, bad-ass gangsters, Mexican stand-offs, Italian surnames, cunning plots, poison, handguns, sonnets and fast-paced dialogue laden with pop culture references and extended metaphors - all in a plot with more twists than a night at Jack Rabbit Slims. It’s an improvised comedy mash-up that blows audiences away.\r\n\r\n<q>“Forsooth \'twas devilish fun.”</q> – <cite>PRESTO Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“Packs enough comedy to appeal to anyone”</q> - <cite>CANTA</cite>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/uncut.jpg\" alt=\"Scriptless Uncut\" title=\"Scriptless Uncut\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-161\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Scriptless Uncut</h2>\r\n<em>16 May – 14 June 2008</em>\r\n\r\nWith the glitz and glamour of a Hollywood awards ceremony, The Jesters romp across genres, styles and the bounds of political correctness to create anything from art-house, melodrama and independent film to schlock horror, science fiction and big-budget blockbusters, armed with only their wits (and audience suggestions) to guide them. <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite> is a love letter to an industry that shoots too many pictures and not enough actors.\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/chatterbox.jpg\" alt=\"Chatterbox\" title=\"Chatterbox\" width=\"280\" height=\"145\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-168\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Chatterbox</h2>\r\n<em>31 August — 29 September 2007</em>\r\n\r\nThe stars of today are lampooned by the stars of tomorrow as The Court Jesters got up close and personal with local celebrities. After a live interview with Artistic Director Ross Gumbley, four of our top improvisers replay stories from the lives and careers of these famous Cantabrians. Guests include Garry Moore, Margaret Mahy, Steve Gurney, David McPhail and Ruth Dyson.\r\n<h2>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</h2>\r\n<em>7 – 19 July 2007</em>\r\n\r\nEver wondered what your Mad Old Auntie keeps in her trunk?  For the three kids in <cite>Aunty McDuff’s Magical Trunk</cite>, it’s everything they need to escape the boredom of a rainy day and get carried away on a magical adventure that has them cruising the world in a boat or a plane, defending castles, or riding in wagon trains with cowboys and indians! No two shows are the same as the audience help decide what happens next in a unique adventure in storytelling using the magic of imagination.\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pull-out pull-8 span-8\"><img src=\"http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/haha.jpg\" alt=\"Radio Ha Ha\" title=\"Radio Ha Ha\" width=\"150\" height=\"200\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-166\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Radio Ha Ha</h2>\r\n<em>27 April — 26 May 2007</em>\r\n\r\nA rapid-fire, off-the-cuff 1930s radio show shaped entirely around audience suggestions to create news, interviews and thrilling serials that never seen – or heard - before. Packed with thrills and spills and complete with live sound effects and music, this loving homage to the golden age of the wireless proved so popular that it was aired on Radio NZ National.','Past Shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-1