es the style and language of Shakespeare and pumps it up with the characters and the pop-culture references of Tarantino,” says Cooper, “then ups the ante by being entirely improvised”. \r\n\r\nFor those unfamiliar with the unique insanity that is improv, Cooper is happy to explain, saying, “The cast weave seemingly random suggestions together, spouting Shakespearean verse all the way. Like <cite>Pulp Fiction</cite>, the narrative might not be linear - it may, for instance, flash back in time to show how one character developed an audience-suggested fear of clowns. The result is a plot with more twists than a night at Jack Rabbit Slims”.\r\n\r\nRehearsals have been packed with star-crossed lovers, bad-ass gangsters, Mexican stand-offs, Italian surnames, cunning plots, poison, handguns, sonnets and protracted speeches with extended metaphors. The cast call the result a “leaner, meaner, faster and funnier production than anything we’ve done before”. Those worried about bad language need not worry – all swearing is Shakespearean, so “only those fluent in 16th Century English will be offended”, adds Cooper.\r\n\r\nShakespeare scholars, film buffs or fans of improv comedy, PULP WILLIAM has something for everyone. \r\n\r\n<q>“Manic madness that never missed a beat... forsooth ’twas devilish fun.”</q> – <cite>PRESTO Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“Packs enough comedy to appeal to anyone”</q> – <cite>Canta Magazine</cite>\r\n\r\n<q>“A goodly chuckle indeed”</q> – <cite><a href=\"http://www.theatreview.org.nz/reviews/review.php?id=1275\">Theatreview</a></cite>\r\n<h3>Canterbury Tour</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>May 13:  Ngaio Marsh Theatre, University of Canterbury; 7:00pm - book at Unimart</li>\r\n	<li>May 14:  Rangiora Town Hall, Rangiora; 7:30pm - book at The Court Theatre</li>\r\n	<li>May 15:  The Gaiety, Akaroa; 7:30pm - book at The Information Centre</li>\r\n	<li>May 16:  The Loons, Lyttelton; 8pm - book at <a href=\"http://www.theloons.co.nz\">www.theloons.co.nz</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTickets: All Canterbury Tickets $15\r\n<h3>Nz Comedy Festival</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>May 20-23:  The Transmission Room; 10pm - Book at TICKETEK (service fee will apply)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTickets: Adults $25 / Concessions $20/ Groups $18 \r\n\r\nFor more information, images or interviews, or to arrange reviewers tickets, contact:\r\n\r\nJeff Clark, Communications Manager\r\nPh: 963 0899\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:education@courttheatre.org.nz\">communications@courttheatre.org.nz</a>\r\n','Upcoming shows',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-9','','','2009-05-10 12:41:03','2009-05-10 00:41:03','',22,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/22-revision-9',0,'revision','',0),(245,1,'2009-05-10 12:45:22','2009-05-10 00:45:22','','The Early Early Late Show',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','inherit','open','open','','eels','','','2009-05-10 12:45:22','2009-05-10 00:45:22','',22,'http://www.courtjesters.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2009/03/eels.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(246,1,'2009-05-10 12:55:47','2009-05-10 00:55:47','<h3>The Early Early Late Show, Friday 14 May</h3>\r\n[player name=\"dan.allan\" role=\"MC\"] [player name=\"vanessa.wells\"] [player name=\"jeff.clark\"] [player name=\"matt.powell\"] [player name=\"patrick.duffy\"] [player name=\"joel.chua\" role=\"Muso\"]\r\n<h3>The Early Early Late Show, Saturday 15 May</h3>\r\n[player name=\"dan.allan\" role=\"MC\"] [player name=\"emma.brittenden\"] [player name=\"kathleen.burns\"] [player name=\"eli.matthewson\"] [player name=\"robbie.hunt\"] [player name=\"hamish.oliver\" role=\"Muso\"]\r\n<h3>The Early Early Late Show, Saturday 15 May</h3>\r\n[player name=\"dan.allan\" role=\"MC\"] [player name=\"vanessa.wells\"] [player name=\"kirsty.gillespie\"] [player name=\"patrick.duffy\"] [player name=\"robbie.hunt\"] [player name=\"michael.bell\" role=\"Muso\"]','Playing this week',1,1,0,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,'','publish','open','open','','playing-this-week','','','2009-05-10 12:57:08','2009-05-10 00:57:08