INSERT INTO `wp_usermeta` VALUES (1,1,'nickname','admin'),(2,1,'rich_editing','true'),(3,1,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(4,1,'admin_color','fresh'),(5,1,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:13:\"administrator\";b:1;}'),(6,1,'wp_user_level','10'),(7,1,'first_name','Court'),(8,1,'last_name','Jesters'),(9,1,'wp_autosave_draft_ids','a:28:{i:-1237494368;i:3;i:-1237494540;i:6;i:-1237494696;i:8;i:-1237494740;i:10;i:-1237494843;i:12;i:-1237497422;i:17;i:-1237497536;i:20;i:-1237497569;i:22;i:-1237497624;i:24;i:-1237497671;i:28;i:-1237497766;i:30;i:-1237497799;i:32;i:-1237497817;i:34;i:-1237497834;i:36;i:-1237497874;i:38;i:-1237497906;i:40;i:-1237497954;i:43;i:-1237497988;i:45;i:-1237596213;i:72;i:-1237596249;i:74;i:-1237599034;i:79;i:-1237713318;i:109;i:-1238645923;i:127;i:-1238647067;i:131;i:-1241912945;i:231;i:-1241914386;i:235;i:-1241916688;i:246;i:-1241917251;i:250;}'),(10,1,'wp_usersettings','m0=o&m1=c&m2=c&m3=o&m4=c&m5=o&m6=o&m7=c&m8=o&m9=o&editor=html&hidetb=1'),(11,1,'wp_usersettingstime','1241918006'),(12,1,'closedpostboxes_page','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(13,1,'metaboxhidden_page','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(14,2,'first_name','Matt'),(15,2,'last_name','Powell'),(16,2,'nickname','Matt'),(17,2,'rich_editing','true'),(18,2,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(19,2,'admin_color','fresh'),(20,2,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:13:\"administrator\";b:1;}'),(21,2,'wp_user_level','10'),(22,2,'description','Matt found his way into a High School Theatre Sports final when his school team\'s reserve broke his arm, and bravely essayed a Welsh accent in a scene about coal miners. He spent several years learning, and later teaching, improvisation at university, representing the University of Canterbury at both local and national levels, before joining the Court Jesters in late 2002. As well as Scared Scriptless, Matt has appeared in several Jesters shows, including <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite>, <cite>A Very Merry Scriptless</cite>, and <cite>Chatterbox</cite>, and has variously acted, written, and directed for DramaSoc, Musoc, Canterbury Children\'s Theatre, and Christchurch Repertory Theatre. In 2007, Matt adapted Shakespeare\'s <cite>Tempest</cite> as the Court Theatre\'s school touring show, <cite>The Magic Island</cite>. A strong narrative player with skills in wordplay, music and physicality, Matt can also be seen performing with the acclaimed Latin Fire dance troupe.'),(23,3,'first_name','Kirsty'),(24,3,'last_name','Gillespie'),(25,3,'nickname','Kirsty'),(26,3,'rich_editing','true'),(27,3,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(28,3,'admin_color','fresh'),(29,3,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(30,3,'wp_user_level','7'),(31,4,'first_name','Emma'),(32,4,'last_name','Brittenden'),(33,4,'nickname','Emma B'),(34,4,'rich_editing','true'),(35,4,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(36,4,'admin_color','fresh'),(37,4,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:13:\"administrator\";b:1;}'),(38,4,'wp_user_level','10'),(39,5,'first_name','Jeff'),(40,5,'last_name','Clark'),(41,5,'nickname','Jeff'),(42,5,'rich_editing','true'),(43,5,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(44,5,'admin_color','fresh'),(45,5,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(46,5,'wp_user_level','7'),(47,6,'first_name','Brendon'),(48,6,'last_name','Bennetts'),(49,6,'nickname','Brendon'),(50,6,'rich_editing','true'),(51,6,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(52,6,'admin_color','fresh'),(53,6,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(54,6,'wp_user_level','7'),(55,6,'description','Brendon has been improvising with the Court Jesters since 2003. On stage, he is known for his dry wit and storytelling flair. As an MC and director, he is known for innovative shows and formats, including the creation of the improvised Shakespearean gangster show <cite>Pulp William</cite>. Brendon is also one of the Jesters\' most experienced tutors, teaching workshops on improvised theatre, team building, body language, and presentation skills. In his spare time, Brendon is a stand up comedian, an actor, and a writer.'),(56,3,'description','Kirsty started playing Theatre Sports when it was first introduced into Christchurch in 1991, while teaching and finishing her B.Ed. Since then, she has been entranced by the thrill of improvisation, performing at the Court in between stints writing and directing musicals, hosting and managing shows for CTV, and running the TV promo department of Telstra Clear in Wellington. As one of Lion Breweries\' top salespeople, Kirsty has had a varied and successful career in both the corporate arena and running her own business. She returned to the Court as a professional improviser in 2002, and became manager of the Jesters in 2005. She has been the main thrust in seeing the Court Jesters achieve weekly sell-out shows of Scared Scriptless, and has developed a respected corporate following, organising over 100 corporate events a year. As well as Scared Scriptless, Kirsty has featured in <cite>Radio HaHa</cite> and <cite>A Very Merry Scriptless</cite>.'),(57,7,'first_name','Daniel'),(58,7,'last_name','Bain'),(59,7,'nickname','Dan B'),(60,7,'rich_editing','true'),(61,7,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(62,7,'admin_color','fresh'),(63,7,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(64,7,'wp_user_level','7'),(65,7,'description','Since graduating from two years at CircoArts circus training school, Daniel has worked as a clown, contortionist, comedian, juggler, magician, human chopping block, and stilt acrobat in circus tents, street corners, and cabarets the world around. He has been a member of the Court Jesters for the last six years, regularly performing in <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite> and at corporate events as an improviser. He is also a stand-up comedian, taking his two man variety show <cite>Sharp</cite> to the New Zealand International Comedy Festival ’07 and <cite>Orphans of Comedy</cite> to the ’09 Festival, and is regularly seen behind microphones in Christchurch. He has been a familiar face at the Court Theatre, performing lead roles in every one of their 2008 kids\' shows, and the critically acclaimed <cite>Pulp William</cite>.'),(67,4,'description','Emma has been performing with the Court Jesters since 2003, when she joined as the company\'s then youngest member.Since the she has appeared at The Court in several productions, including <cite>Chatterbox</cite> and the children\'s holiday show, <cite>Auntie McDuff\'s Magical Trunk</cite>. Emma holds an ATCL (Tchng) in Speech and Drama and a BA majoring in Latin and Maori. She is an experienced drama and improvisation coach, and currently teaches the intermediate and senior drama classes at The Court, where she works full-time in charge of the Education programme, liaising with schools and young people.'),(66,5,'description','Known for his \"lightning wit\" on stage, Jeff has been a regular performer in SCARED SCRIPTLESS for over a decade, building a wealth of experience in corporate entertainment as he goes. Jeff has worked as a tutor to various ages and groups throughout the country, and gained the role of Education Manager for the Court Theatre in 2006. Jeff is currently helping to promote The Court\'s activities as Communications Manager. A love of writing and storytelling has always been a guiding force for Jeff, and, after several successful forays into writing and directing children\'s theatre, television and sketch comedy, his first full-length play, <cite>A True Account of the Regrettable Circumstances and Mysterious Demise of Edgar Allan Poe</cite>, will debut in The Forge in September 2009.'),(68,8,'first_name','Patrick'),(69,8,'last_name','Duffy'),(70,8,'nickname','Patrick'),(71,8,'rich_editing','true'),(72,8,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(73,8,'admin_color','fresh'),(74,8,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(75,8,'wp_user_level','7'),(76,8,'description','Patrick is the Swiss Army Knife of the theatre world, an actor, director, designer, improviser, an international corporate entertainer, Cleverfool and self appointed Executive Smartypants. Over the last 20 years Patrick has continued to make his mark on the theatre scene. He was one of the founding members of the Court Jesters, has performed throughout New Zealand, Australia, and Europe with the international comedy duo The Shenanigan Brothers, and was instrumental in the creation of the World Buskers\' Festival. His involvement with various Court Theatre productions ranges from actor to director, devisor of his own works and children’s shows, and has included stints as both set and costume designer. As a designer he has gained international recognition and success as a multi award winner at the Wearable Art awards.'),(77,9,'first_name','Daniel'),(78,9,'last_name','Allan'),(79,9,'nickname','Dan A'),(80,9,'rich_editing','true'),(81,9,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(82,9,'admin_color','fresh'),(83,9,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(84,9,'description','Daniel is a highly experienced improvisor, showing natural flair as a wee lad when Theatre Sports was first taking root in Christchurch. Dan brings acting skills to his improv, having performed in local theatre with reckless abandon over the past decade, including the Wellington Fringe ’07,  physical theatre success with <cite>Fleet</cite>, and Musoc\'s production of <cite>Hair</cite>. On the improv stage, Dan is an all-rounder, valued as much for his charming MCing as for his quirky character creations. Daniel is also a secondary school teacher, and, when he is not teaching or improvising, might be glimpsed concocting experimental theatre with his partner Lisa.'),(85,9,'wp_user_level','7'),(86,10,'first_name','Robbie'),(87,10,'last_name','Hunt'),(88,10,'nickname','Robbie'),(89,10,'rich_editing','true'),(90,10,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(91,10,'admin_color','fresh'),(92,10,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:6:\"editor\";b:1;}'),(93,10,'wp_user_level','7'),(94,10,'description','After leading Burnside to junior and senior crowns in the high school Theatre Sports competition, Robbie joined the Court Jesters in 1995. After a decade sojourn to Wellington to train at Toi Whakaari/New Zealand Drama School, and to tend bar, Robbie returned to the warm embrace of Christchurch and the Jesters in 2007. Since then, Robbie has toured the country with his award-winning one-man play, <cite>Good Enough?</cite>, and worked extensively throughout New Zealand and abroad with Capital E! children\'s theatre. Currently, Robbie manages Mod\'s Hair in Merivale, and has the biggest cat you\'re ever likely to see. He\'s just big boned! Robbie is a good Kiwi man, loves beer, rugby, can fix anything, swears like a sailor, looks great in short shorts, and irons a fine straight crease. Robbie enjoys long walks on the beach and fish and chips, and is looking for a good dog to share these wonderful things with.'),(95,11,'first_name','Daniel'),(96,11,'last_name','Pengelly'),(97,11,'nickname','Pengelly'),(98,11,'rich_editing','true'),(99,11,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(100,11,'admin_color','fresh'),(101,11,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(102,11,'wp_user_level','1'),(103,11,'description','Pengelly has been with the Court Jesters since 2004. He is energised by teaching and is involved with Theatresports and improvisation classes from 5-year-olds to adults. He is a cheeky and charismatic MC and focuses on creating the right environment for the right situation. He is a qualified chef, works as an event manager and, in 2009, will complete his degree in Human Resource Management. He has had his own small farming business and currently runs his own catering service. In 2008, Pengelly performed in a Court Theatre kids\' show, with ShowBiz Canterbury in <cite>Chicago</cite>, and in 2009, <cite>Miss Saigon</cite>. Pengelly combines his event management and organisation skills with his corporate acting work and specialises in roaming characters at events.'),(104,12,'first_name','Emma'),(105,12,'last_name','Cusdin'),(106,12,'nickname','Emma C'),(107,12,'rich_editing','true'),(108,12,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(109,12,'admin_color','fresh'),(110,12,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(111,12,'wp_user_level','1'),(112,12,'description','Emma has been a member of the Court Jesters since 2007, on the tail end of 5 years of Theatre Sports in school. Though a fresh face to the company, she has made her mark especially in the realm of children\'s entertainment, having worked on the children\'s show <cite>What Now?</cite> for the last 2 years as a voice actor. She is heavily involved in Christchurch theatre as an actor and a director, and her passion for Shakespeare saw her perform on the stage at the Globe Theatre in London with Shakespeare Globe Centre New Zealand. Emma has taught Theatre Sports and drama to school students for 5 years now, and always relishes the opportunity to teach others.'),(113,13,'first_name','Javier'),(114,13,'last_name','Jarquin'),(115,13,'nickname','Jav'),(116,13,'rich_editing','true'),(117,13,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(118,13,'admin_color','fresh'),(119,13,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(120,13,'wp_user_level','1'),(121,13,'description','You name it and he’s probably done it. Since joining the Court Jesters in 2003, Javier has worked as an improvisor, actor, MC, comedian, tutor, magician, director, writer, choreographer, and more. An entertainer through and through, he has literally performed in hundreds of comedy shows and corporate events. As a full time performer, highlights include <cite>The New Zealand International Comedy Festival</cite>, <cite>Pulp William</cite>, <cite>The History Boys</cite>, <cite>The Cape</cite>, <cite>What Now</cite>, <cite>The New Zealand Improv Fest</cite>, and countless improv shows, children’s productions and films around the country. On stage, Javier is known for his physical energy, strong presence, slick execution and most importantly his professionalism.'),(122,14,'first_name','Andrew'),(123,14,'last_name','Todd'),(124,14,'nickname','Andrew'),(125,14,'rich_editing','true'),(126,14,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(127,14,'admin_color','fresh'),(128,14,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(129,14,'wp_user_level','1'),(130,14,'description','Andrew joined the Court Jesters in 2006, which precipitated regular appearances in <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite>, as well as in various get-ups as a corporate entertainer. He is particularly skilled in the areas of character creation, accents and voice acting, and storytelling. Outside the Jesters, he has written, directed, and/or performed in numerous scripted and improvised shows with Dramasoc, the Loopen Experiment, and Liminal Theatre (which he co-founded), as well as appearing in the 2008 World Buskers\' Festival. He also works as an AV and Sound designer for the Court Theatre, has a regular movie review spot on RDU, records music as The Hairy Nobs, and is studying towards a BFA in Film.'),(131,15,'first_name','Vanessa'),(132,15,'last_name','Wells'),(133,15,'nickname','Vanessa'),(134,15,'rich_editing','true'),(135,15,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(136,15,'admin_color','fresh'),(137,15,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(138,15,'wp_user_level','1'),(139,15,'description','Vanessa is an actor who first let go of a script in 2005 and has been improvising with The Court Jesters ever since. As well as being an an improviser and MC, Vanessa balances a family life with other theatre, television, radio and tutoring work.  She happily works with or without a script!  Hosting CTV\'s <cite>Good Living</cite> in 2007/08 brought her into Canterbury homes as a popular television presenter.  Vanessa is professional, versatile, and brings a warmth and genuine naturalness to the stage.'),(140,16,'first_name','Michael'),(141,16,'last_name','Bell'),(142,16,'nickname','Michael'),(143,16,'rich_editing','true'),(144,16,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(145,16,'admin_color','fresh'),(146,16,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(147,16,'wp_user_level','1'),(148,16,'description','Winner of national composition and performance awards in classical, choral, jazz and rock genres, Michael writes, arranges, records and produces music for New Zealand TV, film, radio, CD, live music performance, theatre and other media through Orange Studio. He writes for orchestras, including the Christchurch Symphony and Vector Wellington Orchestras, writes regularly for <cite>What Now</cite>, and has scored 18 short films and 3 feature films. He holds a Bachelor of Music with a double major in composition/arrangement and performance. Michael has been accompanying improvised comedy since 2003 and has been a member of the Court Jesters since 2005.'),(149,17,'first_name','Eli'),(150,17,'last_name','Matthewson'),(151,17,'nickname','Eli'),(152,17,'rich_editing','true'),(153,17,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(154,17,'admin_color','fresh'),(155,17,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(156,17,'wp_user_level','1'),(157,17,'description','Eli is the youngest member of the Court Jesters, after being introduced into the company in mid 2007. Eli\'s greatest asset is his versatility: he is a strong singer, an experienced actor, and a charming, low-key MC. He has performed all over Christchurch, in anything from Shakespeare and musicals to children\'s theatre and corporate events. As a Theatre Sports tutor, Eli brings energy to a class and inspires students to try new things. Eli has most of an English degree, and is also employed by the University of Canterbury as a performer for a series of educational plays that have toured around the South Island.'),(185,21,'first_name','Scott'),(158,18,'first_name','Alice'),(159,18,'last_name','Canton'),(160,18,'nickname','Alice'),(161,18,'rich_editing','true'),(162,18,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(163,18,'admin_color','fresh'),(164,18,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(165,18,'wp_user_level','1'),(166,18,'description','Alice has been working professionally as a tutor, improvisor, and corporate entertainer for the Court Jesters since 2003. Highlights with the company include The Forge seasons of <cite>Chatterbox</cite> and <cite>Scriptless Uncut</cite>, as well as the weekly show <cite>Scared Scriptless</cite>. She is particularly passionate about using improvisation and movement as a tool to encourage self awareness and confidence in her younger students, taking regular teaching spots in holiday programmes, dance courses and schools. Alice is also an accomplished musician, and plays with various groups as a percussionist and pianist. Having recently completed a Bachelor of Fine Arts, she spends most days fantasising about sculptures.'),(167,19,'first_name','Hamish'),(168,19,'last_name','Oliver'),(169,19,'nickname','Hamish'),(170,19,'rich_editing','true'),(171,19,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(172,19,'admin_color','fresh'),(173,19,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(174,19,'wp_user_level','1'),(175,19,'description','Hamish has a Master\'s degree in composition and is a freelance composer, arranger, musical director and performer for television, film and theatre. He has been performing music for improvised drama for thirteen years with the Improvisors in Wellington and the Court Jesters and the Outwits in Christchurch, and is known for his enthusiasm for weaving well-known film and TV theme music into improvised scenes. He lectures courses in digital audio software and music theory at Canterbury University, Christchurch Polytechnic, and the Music and Audio Institute of New Zealand. Hamish has performed with Hayley Westenra, Serj Tankian, Bic Runga, Aled Jones, Anika Moa, Michael Barrymore, Christchurch Symphony, and Auckland Philharmonia Orchestra among others. In 2008, he was Musical Director for an Australian tour by Aled Jones and also for musicals at the Court Theatre, NASDA (National Academy of Singing and Dramatic Arts), and Showbiz Christchurch. He was composer for the Court Theatre productions of <cite>Under Milk Wood</cite> in 2008 and <cite>The Raft</cite> in 2007, and has composed for a feature film and several TV series and short films.'),(176,20,'first_name','Joel'),(177,20,'last_name','Chua'),(178,20,'nickname','Joel'),(179,20,'rich_editing','true'),(180,20,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(181,20,'admin_color','fresh'),(182,20,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(183,20,'wp_user_level','1'),(184,20,'description','Joel Chua is a music student (at Jazz School, CPIT) and freelance musician who has enjoyed numerous jazz gigs around Christchurch, including the Outdoor Film Series at The Arts Centre, the Premiere Garden Party for the Ellerslie International Flower Show and the Jazz@6pm series (part of the New Zealand International Jazz &amp; Blues Festival \'09). Aside from performing, Joel is also a competent teacher, having provided peer support for some first year students in Jazz school.'),(186,21,'last_name','Koorey'),(187,21,'nickname','Scott'),(188,21,'rich_editing','true'),(189,21,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(190,21,'admin_color','fresh'),(191,21,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(192,21,'wp_user_level','1'),(193,21,'description','Scott has been involved with the performing arts in Christchurch since\r\nthe mid-1990s, as an actor, director, writer and composer. He is also\r\na regular fixture in the Christchurch standup comedy scene. At the\r\nCourt Theatre, in addition to being a member of the Court Jesters, he\r\nhas appeared in a number of the Court\'s kids\' shows. Scott has\r\nextensive experience as an event host, regularly MCing <cite>Scared\r\nScriptless</cite>, compering quiz nights around town, and hosting the\r\nnighttime Ghost Walks around the Arts Centre. Scott has a strong and\r\nexpressive singing and speaking voice, is capable of growing facial\r\nhair rapidly, and is rather tall.'),(194,22,'first_name','Kathleen'),(195,22,'last_name','Burns'),(196,22,'nickname','Kathleen'),(197,22,'rich_editing','true'),(198,22,'comment_shortcuts','false'),(199,22,'admin_color','fresh'),(200,22,'wp_capabilities','a:1:{s:11:\"contributor\";b:1;}'),(201,22,'wp_user_level','1'),(202,22,'description','Kathleen has been a member of the Court Jesters since 2004, and whether performing on the stage as an improviser, singer or an MC, her bold comedic flair remains untameable. Her compelling confidence combined with theatrical artistry ensures a good time for any audience, anywhere. She also loves to spread the magic, and has experience teaching people of all age levels and skill levels.  Kathleen is looking forward to completing her Bachelor of Performing Arts degree at NASDA in 2009.');
